<references/>

*Upgrades to melee gear should be prioritised over mage gear upgrades.
*Although the [[Scythe of vitur]] provides higher overall DPS, the [[Inquisitor's mace]] performs similarly and has no cost in charges. Without any pieces of Inquisitor's armour, the mace outperforms the scythe.
*Whether granite maul or dragon claws are more effective as the special weapon depends on other gear. With a scythe, the maul is better than claws if using Inquisitor's top and bottom, or with a bludgeon, if using full Inquisitor's armour. With this in mind, dragon claws are also easier to use; if you tend to miss attack ticks with the maul, claws are more effective.
*The [[elder maul]] can be substituted for any godsword that is set to the crush attack style to one-hit parasites.
*For mage armour, as the pillars have no defence, only armour with [[Highest_bonuses#Magic_damage|magic damage bonus]] has any effect. The priority for these are: [[occult necklace]] > [[imbued heart]] (if using a [[powered staff]]) > [[tormented bracelet]] > [[God_capes#Imbuing|imbued god capes]] and [[ancestral robes]].
*For less experienced players who are not fully comfortable with the boss, substitute some [[anglerfish]] and [[divine super combat potion]]s for regular [[super combat potion]]s and [[Saradomin brews]], and do not bring [[ancestral robes]] pieces to have more supplies.
*If using thralls, the ghost (Magic) thrall is the best to use because it benefits from the double damage on totems.
{{Clear}}

==Tips==
[[File:Phosani's Nightmare corner rifting.gif|thumb|A player demonstrating the corner rifting technique.]]
*During the last Grasping Claws after a Spore special attack, the rifts will never spawn on where a spore was so the player can safely move to one of those tiles without the concern of being hit.
*If husks spawn, kill the bulkier Ranged one first then the Magic one after. This allows the player to use protection prayers from both Phosani's Nightmare and husks. However if they are to spawn on the fourth phase, their initial attacks are delayed slightly. If Phosani's Nightmare uses a melee attack right after spawning, it will hit the player on the same [[RuneScape clock|tick]] as the Magic-using husk so this should be considered if it would be better to kill the skinnier Magic husk first instead as the player tends to have less Magic defence than Ranged. 
*Be sure to have 100% special attack at the start of the final phase, as it is imperative to kill the boss quickly during this phase.
*An advanced technique for players to easily dodge rifts prior to charging totems is to attack Phosani's Nightmare from any ordinal direction (NW, NE, SW, SE). Bearing in mind the big rift under her, if players stand on the edge of the boss on one of these tiles, it will not hit the player should no small rift be under them. The player can keep stepping between an outer tile and the ordinal tile as rifts will not spawn there unless the player was previously stood on it. This technique requires tick-perfect execution and is not recommended for players with high ping.
*Keep in mind that in order to one hit both husks and parasites, your max hit has to equal or be above their health (20 and 55 HP respectively). In order to guarantee a one hit kill, make sure you are wearing your melee gear, praying piety and are boosted by your combat potion. In this fashion, an event RPG or Ham Joint will not be able to kill the parasite seeing as the max hit will never be above 30. For this reason an elder maul/godsword must be used for the parasites.
*If using a [[powered staff]], make sure to use the long range attack style. Since the totems give no experience whatsoever, the extra few tiles in attack range makes attacking the totems significantly easier; using accurate provides no advantage.

